==English==
===Etymology===
From [[French]] ''[[poignard]]'' ([[dagger]]), from ''[[poign]]'' ([[fist]]), from [[Old French]], from Latin ''[[pugnus]]''. See {{pie|peuk-}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
# A [[dagger]] typically having a [[slender]] [[square]] or [[triangular]] [[blade]].

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}
#To stab with a poniard.

